cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DS

The paper discusses the adoption of big data platforms and distributed computing for formal verification, which falls under the category of computer science logic (cs.LO). The use of MapReduce as the core computational model suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The mention of different modelling formalisms hints at programming languages (cs.PL) and the use of Petri-nets as benchmark specifications suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
